obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (5927)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5927&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Indian Nursing Council`
  line `Act, 1947.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force at once.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 45 of 1957, s. 2, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31-10-`
  line `2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (5928)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Interpretation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5928&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(a) "the Council" means the ^1[Council] constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "prescribed" means prescribed by regulations made under section 16;”`
  line
  line `(c) "`
  line `^2[State] Council" means a Council (by whatever name called) constituted under the law of a`
  line `^2[State] to regulate the registration of nurses, midwives or health visitors in the ^3[State];`
  line
  line `(d) "`
  line `^2[State] register" means a register of nurses, midwives or health visitors maintained under the`
  line `law of a ^3[State].`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Indian Council of Nursing" (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Provincial".`
  line
  line `3. Subs. ibid., for "Province".`
  line
  line `4. Omitted by Act 45 of 1957, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (5929)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution and composition of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5929&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, as soon as`
  line `may be, constitute a Council consisting of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) one nurse enrolled in a ^1[State] register elected by each ^1[State] Council;`
  line
  line `^2[(b) two members elected from among themselves by the heads of institutions recognised by the`
  line `Council for the purpose of this clause in which training is given--`
  line
  line `(i) for obtaining a University degree in nursing; or`
  line
  line `(ii) in respect of a post-certificate course in the teaching of nursing and in nursing`
  line administration;]
  line
  line `(c) one member elected from among themselves by the heads of institutions in which health`
  line `visitors are trained;`
  line
  line `(d) one member elected by the Medical Council of India;`
  line
  line `(e) one member elected by the Central Council of the Indian Medical Association;`
  line
  line `(f) one member elected by the Council of the Trained Nurses Association of India;`
  line
  line `^3[(g) one midwife or auxiliary nurse-midwife enrolled in a State register, elected by each of the`
  line `State Councils in the four groups of States mentioned below, each group of States being taken in`
  line `rotation in the following order, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) Kerala, Madhya Pradesh and ^4[Uttar Pradesh and Haryana],`
  line
  line `(ii) Andhra Pradesh, Bihar, ^5[Maharashtra] and Rajasthan,`
  line
  line `(iii) ^6[Karnataka], Punjab ^7[Himachal Pradesh] and West Bengal,`
  line
  line `(iv) Assam, ^8[Gujarat] ^9[Tamil Nadu] and Orissa;]`
  line
  line `(h) the Director General of Health Services, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(i) the Chief Principal Matron, Medical Directorate, General Headquarters, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(j) the Chief Nursing Superintendent, office of the Director General of Health Services, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(k) the Director of Maternity and Child Welfare, Indian Red Cross Society, ex officio;`
  line
  line `^10[(l) the Chief Administrative Medical Officer (by whatever name called) of each State other than`
  line `a Union territory, ex officio;]`
  line
  line `^11[(m) the Superintendent of Nursing services (by whatever name called), ex officio, from each of`
  line `the States in the two groups mentioned below, each group of States being taken in rotation in the`
  line `following order, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) Andhra Pradesh, Assam, ^5[Maharashtra], Madhya Pradesh, ^9[Tamil Nadu], Uttar`
  line `Pradesh^12[West Bengal and Haryana].`
  line
  line `(ii) Bihar, ^13 [Gujarat], ^7[Himachal Pradesh], Kerala, ^6[Karnataka], Orissa, Punjab and`
  line Rajasthan;]
  line
  line `(n) four members nominated by the Central Government, of whom at least two shall be nurses,`
  line `midwives or health visitors enrolled in ^14[State] register and one shall be experienced educationalist;`
  line
  line `^15[(o) three members elected by Parliament, two by the House of the People from among its`
  line `members and the other by the Council of States from among its members.]`
  line
  line `(2) The President of the Council shall be elected by the members of the Council from among`
  line `themselves:`
  line
  line `Provided that for five years from the first constitution of the Council the President shall be a person`
  line `nominated from amongst the members of the Council by the Central Government, who shall hold office`
  line `during the pleasure of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) No act done by the Council shall be questioned on the ground merely of the existence of any`
  line `vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Provincial".`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for clause (b) (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 45 of 1957, s. 4, for clause (g) (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by the Punjab Reorganisation and Delhi High Court (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1968, for "and`
  line `Uttar Pradesh" (w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by the Bombay Reorganisation (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1961, for "Bombay" (w.e.f. 1-5-1960).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Mysore State (Alteration of Name) (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subject) order, 1974, for "Mysore" (w.e.f. 1-11-`
  line `1973).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by the State of Himachal Pradesh (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1973, (w.e.f. 25-1-1971).`
  line
  line `8. Subs.by the Bombay Reorganisation(Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1961, for "Madras and Orissa" (w.e.f. 1-5-`
  line `1960).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by the Madras State (Alteration of Name) (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order.1970, for "Madras" (w.e.f. 14-`
  line `1-1969).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 45 of 1957, s.4, for clause (l) (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by s.4, ibid., for clause (m) (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by the Punjab Reorganisation and Delhi High Court (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1968, for "and`
  line `West Bengal" (w.e.f. 1-11-1966).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by the Bombay Reorganisation (Adaptation of Laws on Union Subjects) Order, 1961, (w.e.f. 1-5-1960)`
  line
  line `14.Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Provincial".`
  line
  line `15. Subs. by Act 45 of 1957, s.4, for clause (o) (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (5930)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Incorporation of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5930&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Council constituted under section 3 shall be a body corporate`
  line `by the name of the Indian Nursing Council, having perpetual succession and a common seal, with power`
  line `to acquire property both-movable and immovable, and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (5931)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Mode of elections.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Provincial".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5931&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Elections under sub-section (1) of section 3 by ^1[State] Councils shall be`
  line `conducted in accordance with rules made in this behalf by the respective ^1[State] Governments, and where`
  line `any dispute arises regarding any such election it shall be referred to the ^1[State] Government concerned`
  line `whose decision shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) Other elections under that sub-section shall be conducted in the prescribed manner, and where any`
  line `dispute arises regarding any such election, it shall be referred to the Central Government whose decision`
  line `shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (5932)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office and casual vacancies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Omitted by Act 45 of 1957, s. 5, (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5932&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, an elected or`
  line `nominated member, other than a nominated President, shall hold office for a term of five years from the`
  line `date of his election or nomination or until his successor has been duly elected or nominated, whichever is`
  line longer.
  line
  line `(2) An elected or nominated member may at any time resign his membership by writing under his`
  line `hand addressed to the President, and the seat of such member shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(3) An elected or nominated member shall be deemed to have vacated his seat if he is absent without`
  line `excuse sufficient in the opinion of the Council from three consecutive meetings of the Council where the`
  line `interval between the first and third of the said meetings exceeds six months.`
  line
  line `(4) A casual vacancy in the Council shall be filled by fresh election or nomination, as the case may be`
  line `and the person elected or nominated to fill the vacancy shall hold office only for the remainder of the term`
  line `for which the member whose place he takes was elected or nominated.`
  line
  line `(5) Members of the Council shall be eligible for re-election or re-nomination.`
  line
  line `^1* * * * *`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (5933)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title Meetings.
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5933&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall hold its first meeting at such time and place as may be appointed`
  line `by the President, and thereafter the Council shall meet at such time and place as may be appointed by the`
  line Council.
  line
  line `(2) Until otherwise prescribed, ten members of the Council shall form a quorum, and all the acts of`
  line `the Council shall be decided by a majority of the members present and voting.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (5934)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Officers, committees and servants of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5934&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Secretary of the Council (who may`
  line `also, if it is deemed expedient by the Council, act as Treasurer) shall, for three years from the first`
  line `constitution of the Council, be a person appointed by the Central Government and shall hold office during`
  line `the pleasure of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall--`
  line
  line `(a) elect from among its members a Vice-President;`
  line
  line `(b) constitute from among its members an Executive Committee and such other committees`
  line `for general or special purposes as the Council deems necessary to carry out the purposes of this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(c) subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), appoint a Secretary, who may also, if deemed`
  line `expedient, act as Treasurer;`
  line
  line `(d) appoint or nominate such other officers and servants as the Council deems necessary to`
  line `carry out the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) require and take from the Secretary, or from any other officer or servant, such security for`
  line `the due performance of his duties as the Council deems necessary;`
  line
  line `(f) with the previous sanction of the Central Government, fix the fees and allowances to be`
  line `paid to the President, Vice-President and members and the pay and allowances of officers and`
  line `servants of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (5935)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `The Executive Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5935&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Executive Committee shall consist of nine members, of`
  line `whom seven shall be elected by the Council from among its members.`
  line
  line `(2) The President and Vice-President of the Council shall be members ex officio of the Executive`
  line `Committee, and shall be President and Vice-President, respectively, of that Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) In addition to the powers and duties conferred and imposed upon it by this Act, the Executive`
  line `Committee shall exercise and discharge such powers and duties as the Council may confer or impose`
  line `upon it by any regulations which may be made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (5936)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Recognition of qualifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5936&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of this Act, the qualifications included`
  line `in^1[Part I of] the Schedule shall be recognised qualifications, and the qualifications included in Part II of`
  line `the Schedule shall be recognised higher qualifications.`
  line
  line `(2) Any authority within the ^2[States]`
  line `^3*** which, being recognised by the ^4[State] Government ^1[in`
  line `consultation with the State Council, if any,] for the purpose of granting any qualification, grants a`
  line `qualification in general nursing, midwifery, ^1[auxiliary nursing-midwifery] health visiting or public health`
  line `nursing, not included in the Schedule may apply to the Council to have such qualification recognised, and`
  line `the Council may declare that such qualification, or such qualification only when granted after a specified`
  line `date shall be a recognised qualification for the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council may enter into negotiations with any authority ^5[in any ^6[territory of India to which`
  line `this Act does not extend] or foreign country] ^3[* * *] which by the law of ^7[such territory] or country is`
  line `entrusted with the maintenance of a register of nurses midwives or health visitors; for the settling of a`
  line `scheme of reciprocity for the recognition of qualifications, and in pursuance of any such scheme the Council may declare that a qualification granted by any authority in any ^8[such territory] or country, or`
  line `such qualification, only when granted after a specified date, shall be a recognised qualification for the`
  line `purposes of this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no declaration shall be made under this sub-section in respect of any qualification`
  line `unless by the law and practice ^9[of the foreign country] in which the qualification is granted persons`
  line `domiciled or originating ^10[in India] ^11*** and holding qualifications recognised under this Act are`
  line `permitted to enter and practice the nursing profession ^12[in that country]:`
  line
  line `Provided further that--`
  line
  line `(i) any reciprocal arrangements subsisting at the date of the commencement of this Act between a`
  line `^13[State] Council and any authority outside India for the recognition of qualifications shall, unless the`
  line `Council decides otherwise, continue in force, and`
  line
  line `^14[(ii) any qualification granted by an authority in a territory of India to which this Act did not`
  line `extend at the date of its commencement and recognised on the said date by the State Council of a`
  line `State to which this Act then extended, shall continue to be a recognised qualification for the purpose`
  line `of registration in that State.]`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sub-sections (2) and (3) and of sections 14 and 15 shall apply mutatis mutandis`
  line `to the declaration by the Council of a qualification granted in respect of post-certificate nursing training`
  line `as a recognised higher qualification.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 45 of 1957, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-12- 1958).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Provinces".`
  line
  line `3. The words "of India" omitted by, ibid.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by A.O. 1950, for "Provincial".`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 75 of 1950, s. 2, "in any State or country outside the States" (w.e.f. 28-12-1950).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3), 1956 for "Part B Slates" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. ibid., for "such State" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by A.O. (No. 3), 1956, for "such State" (w.e.f. 1-11-1956).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 75 of 1950, s. 2, for "of the State or Country" (w.e.f. 28-12-1950).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by, s. 2, ibid., for "in any State" (w.e.f. 28-12-1950).`
  line
  line `11. The words "of India" omitted by the A. O. 1950.`
  line
  line `12. Subs. by Act 75 of 1950. s. 2, for "in that Sate County".`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Provincial".`
  line
  line `14. Subs. by Act 45 of 1957, s. 6, for clause (ii) (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5937)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Effect of recognition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5937&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law,--`
  line
  line `(a) any recognised qualification shall be a sufficient qualification for enrolment in any ^2[State]`
  line register;
  line
  line `(b) no person shall, after the date of commencement of this Act, be entitled to be enrolled in any`
  line `^2[State] register as a nurse, midwife, ^3[auxiliary nurse-midwife], health visitor, or public health nurse`
  line `unless he or she holds a recognised qualification:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person already enrolled in any ^2[State] register before the said date may`
  line `continue to be so enrolled notwithstanding that he or she may not hold a recognised qualification:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any person who was immediately before the said date entitled to be enrolled`
  line `in any ^2[State] register but was not so enrolled shall on application made in this behalf before the`
  line `expiry of two years from the said date be entitled to be enrolled in that register;`
  line
  line `(c) any person holding a recognised higher qualification shall be entitled to have the qualification`
  line `entered as a supplementary qualification in any ^2[State] register in which he or she is enrolled, and`
  line `after the said date no person shall be entitled to have entered as a supplementary qualification in`
  line `any ^2[State] register any qualification which is not a recognised higher qualification.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (b) of sub-section (1)--`
  line
  line `(a) a citizen of India holding a qualification which entitles him or her to be registered with any`
  line `Council of Nursing or Midwifery (by whatever name called) in any foreign country, may, with the`
  line `approval of the Council, be enrolled in any State Register; and where approval has been accorded by`
  line `the Council in respect of such qualification in one case, the approval of the Council for enrolment in a`
  line `State register in the case of any other citizen of India holding the same qualification shall not be`
  line necessary;
  line
  line `(b) a person not being a citizen of India who is employed as a nurse, midwife, auxiliary nursemidwife,`
  line `teacher or administrator in any hospital or institution situated in any State for purposes of`
  line `teaching, research or charitable work may, with the approval of the President of the Council, be`
  line `enrolled temporarily in the State Register for such period as may be specified in this behalf in the`
  line `order issued by the said President:`
  line
  line `Provided that the practice by such person shall be limited to the hospital or institution to which he`
  line `or she is attached.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Section11 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Provincial".`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5938)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to require information as to courses of study and training and examinations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5938&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `authority in any ^1[State] ^2**** which grants a recognised qualification, or a recognised higher`
  line `qualification shall furnish such information as the Council may, from time to time, require as to the`
  line `courses of study and training and examinations to be undergone in order to obtain such qualification, as to`
  line `the ages at which such courses of study and examinations are required to be undergone and such`
  line `qualifications conferred, and generally as to the requisites for obtaining such qualification.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Province".`
  line
  line `2. The words "of India" omitted, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-1-1950).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5939)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title Inspections.
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5939&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Executive Committee may appoint such number of inspectors ^2[whether`
  line `from among members of the Council or otherwise] as it deems necessary to inspect any institution`
  line `recognised as a training institution, and to attend examinations held for the purpose of granting any`
  line `recognised qualification or recognised higher qualification.`
  line
  line `(2) Inspectors appointed under this section shall report to the Executive Committee on the suitability`
  line `of the institution for the purposes of training and on the adequacy of the training therein, or as the case`
  line `may be on the sufficiency of the examinations.`
  line
  line `(3) The Executive Committee shall forward a copy of such report to the authority or institution`
  line `concerned, and shall also forward copies, with the remarks, if any, of the authority or institution`
  line `concerned thereon, to the Central Government and to the ^3[State] Government and ^3[State] Council of the`
  line `^1[State] in which the authority of institution is situated.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Province".`
  line
  line `2. Ins by Act 45 of 1957, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Provincial".`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5940)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Withdrawal of recognition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5940&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) When upon report by the Executive Committee, it appears to`
  line `the Council--`
  line
  line `(a) that the courses of study and training and the examinations to be gone through in order to`
  line `obtain a recognised qualification from any authority in any ^1[State] ^2[* * *], or the conditions for`
  line `admission to such courses or the standards of proficiency required from the candidates at such`
  line `examinations are not in conformity with the regulations made under the Act or fall short of the`
  line `standards required thereby, or`
  line
  line `(b) that an institution recognised by a ^3[State] Council for the training of nurses, midwives`
  line `^4[auxiliary nurse-midwives] or health visitors does not satisfy the requirements of the Council,--`
  line
  line `the Council may send to the Government of the ^1[State] in which the authority or institution, as the case`
  line `may be, is situated a statement to such effect and the ^3[State] Government shall forward it, along with`
  line `such remarks as it may think fit to the authority or institution concerned and, in a case referred to in`
  line `clause (b) to the ^3[State] Council also, with an intimation of the period within which the authority or`
  line `institution may submit its explanation to the ^3[State] Government.`
  line
  line `(2) On the receipt of the explanation or, where no explanation is submitted within the period fixed,`
  line `then on the expiry of the period, the ^3[State] Government shall make its recommendations to the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council, after such further inquiry, if any, as it may think fit to make, and in a case referred to`
  line `in clause (b) of sub-section (1), after considering any remarks which the ^4[State] Council may have`
  line `addressed to it, may declare,--`
  line
  line `(a) in a case referred to in clause (a) of that sub-section, that the qualifications granted by the`
  line `authority concerned shall be recognised qualifications only when granted before a specified date, or`
  line
  line `(b) in a case referred to in the said clause (b), that with effect from a date specified in the`
  line `declaration any person holding a recognised qualification whose period of training and study`
  line `preparatory to the grant to him of the qualification was passed at the institution concerned shall be`
  line `entitled to be registered only in the ^5[State] in which the institution is situated.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council may declare that any recognised qualification granted outside the ^6[States] ^7*** shall`
  line `be a recognised qualification only if granted before a specified date.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Province".`
  line
  line `2. The words "of India" omitted, ibid. (w.e.f. 28-1-1950).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Provincial".`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by, s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by A.O.1950, for "Province".`
  line
  line `6. Subs., ibid., for "Provinces".`
  line
  line `7. The words "of India" omitted by ibid.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5941)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Mode of declaration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5941&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] All declarations under section 10 or section 14 shall be made by`
  line `resolution passed at a meeting of the Council called for the purpose, and shall forthwith be published in`
  line `the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The Central Government shall, from time to time, by notification in the Official Gazette, amend`
  line `the Schedule so as to bring it into accord with any declaration under section 10 or section 14.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 15 re-numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 45 of 1957, s. 10 ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 10, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (5942)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 16
  title `Indian Nurses Register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by ibid., s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-12-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5942&sectionno=15A&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[15A. Indian Nurses Register.--(1) The Council shall cause to be maintained in the prescribed`
  line `manner a register of nurses, midwives, auxiliary nurse-midwives and health visitors to be known as the`
  line `Indian Nurses Register, which shall contain the names of all persons who are for the time being enrolled`
  line `on any State register.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the Secretary of the Council to keep the Indian Nurses Register in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act, and from time to time, to revise the register and publish it in`
  line `the Gazette of India and in, such other manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Such register shall be deemed to be a public document within the meaning of the Indian Evidence`
  line `Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) and may be proved by a copy published in the Gazette of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b:
  sectionId (5943)
  sectionNo 15B
  orderNo 17
  title `Supply of copies of State registers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5943&sectionno=15B&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content:
  string
  line `Each State Council shall supply to the Council twenty`
  line `printed copies of the State register as soon as may be after the 1st day of April of each year and inform`
  line `the Council without delay of all additions to, and other amendments in, the State register made from time`
  line `to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5944)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628&sectionId=5944&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_12_13_00018_194748_1517807325628
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may make regulations not inconsistent with this`
  line `Act generally to carry out the provisions of this Act, and in particular and without prejudice to the`
  line `generality of the foregoing powers, such regulations may provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the management of the property of the Council and the maintenance and audit of its accounts;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which elections referred to in sub-section (2) of section 5 and in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 8 shall be conducted;`
  line
  line `(c) the summoning and holding of the meetings of the Council, the times and places at which`
  line `such meetings shall be held, the conduct of business thereat and the number of members necessary to`
  line `constitute a quorum;`
  line
  line `(d) prescribing the functions of the Executive Committee, the summoning and holding of`
  line `meetings thereof, the times and places at which such meetings shall be held, and the number of`
  line `members necessary to constitute a quorum;`
  line
  line `(e) prescribing the powers and duties of the President and the Vice-President;`
  line
  line `^1[(f) prescribing the tenure of office and the powers and duties of the Secretary and other officers`
  line `and servants of the Council;]`
  line
  line `(ff) prescribing the powers and duties of inspectors;`
  line
  line `(g) prescribing the standard curricula for the training of nurses, midwives and health visitors, for`
  line `training courses for teachers of nurses, midwives and health visitors, and for training in nursing`
  line administration;
  line
  line `(h) prescribing the conditions for admission to courses of training as aforesaid;`
  line
  line `(i) prescribing the standards of examination and other requirements to be satisfied to secure for`
  line `qualifications recognition under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) To enable the Council to be first constituted, the President may, with the previous sanction of the`
  line `Central Government, make regulations of the conduct of the elections referred to in sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 5, and any regulations so made may be altered or rescinded by the Council in exercise of its`
  line `powers under this section.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Every regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid. (w.e. f. 1-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2, and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
